Read Your Qualtrics Data

read.Rmd

üì• Read Your Data

Before reshaping or analyzing your conjoint survey data, you first need to import it into R. In projoint, use the read_Qualtrics() function to quickly read properly formatted Qualtrics files.

üöÄ Quick Workflow

Export your survey responses from Qualtrics

When exporting from Qualtrics:

  • Click ‚ÄúDownload Data‚Äù.
  • Choose CSV format.
  • Critically, select ‚ÄúUse choice text‚Äù instead of coded values.

‚ö° If you skip ‚ÄúUse choice text,‚Äù your conjoint data may not load properly!

Load essential packages 
library(tidyverse)
library(projoint)
Read your CSV file into R using read_Qualtrics() 
# Example: If your file is located in a "data" folder
data <- read_Qualtrics("data/your_file.csv")

Or, if using an example bundled with projoint:

data
